# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .gitignore for the MLP_CUDA study repository
#
# Purpose: keep the repository limited to *source* and *documentation* only.
# Anything that can be regenerated from the source (compiled objects, the final
# executable, the build/ scratch directory) or that is specific to one
# developer's machine (editor settings, OS metadata files) should never be
# committed. This keeps clones small, avoids noisy diffs, and prevents binaries
# built for one GPU/OS from leaking into another contributor's checkout.
#
# Pattern syntax reminders (so a learner can edit this confidently):
#   - A trailing "/" matches a directory only (e.g. "build/").
#   - "*" matches any run of characters within a single path segment.
#   - A leading "/" anchors a pattern to the repo root; without it, the pattern
#     matches in every directory.
#   - Lines starting with "#" are comments; blank lines are ignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Build output -----------------------------------------------------------
# The Makefile compiles each src/*.cu into build/*.o and links build/mlp here,
# and CMake also drops its generated files under build/. The whole directory is
# disposable: `make clean` / a fresh CMake configure recreates it from scratch.
build/

# Object files emitted by nvcc/the host compiler before linking. Ignored
# anywhere (no leading "/") in case someone compiles outside build/.
*.o
*.obj

# Linked executables.
#   - "mlp"   : the Linux/WSL Makefile target name (no extension on POSIX).
#   - "*.exe" : the Windows executable produced by the MSVC + CUDA / CMake build.
mlp
*.exe

# --- Editor / IDE cruft -----------------------------------------------------
# Per-developer editor configuration that must not be shared across the team.
# NOTE on syntax: in .gitignore a '#' only starts a comment when it is the FIRST
# character of a line. A '#' placed AFTER a pattern is treated as part of the
# pattern, not a comment, so each explanation must live on its own line above
# the rule it documents (an inline "build/ # ..." would silently fail to match).
# VS Code workspace settings, launch configs, etc.
.vscode/
# JetBrains (CLion) project metadata.
.idea/
# Vim swap files left behind by an open editor session.
*.swp

# --- OS metadata ------------------------------------------------------------
# Files the operating system sprinkles into directories; never source-relevant.
# macOS Finder folder metadata.
.DS_Store
# Windows Explorer thumbnail cache.
Thumbs.db

# --- Tooling state ----------------------------------------------------------
# Local assistant/agent scratch state (e.g. scheduled-task lock files). This is
# per-machine harness state, not part of the project source.
.claude/

# --- Visual Studio / MSBuild ------------------------------------------------
# Generated when you open/build MLP_CUDA.sln. The .sln/.vcxproj themselves ARE
# committed (they're the project definition); everything below is build output or
# per-user state that must not be.
# Solution Explorer / IntelliSense cache and per-user window state.
.vs/
# Per-user project settings (window layout, local debugger args).
*.user
# Build output + intermediate dirs. OutDir is <repo>\x64\<Config>\ and the CUDA
# build customization keeps its intermediates under <repo>\MLP_CUDA\x64\<Config>\;
# a bare "x64/" (no leading slash) ignores both wherever they appear.
x64/
Win32/
# Debug/PDB databases emitted by the MSVC/CUDA build.
*.pdb
*.idb
*.ilk
